    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-22T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-22T20:00:00-05:00" n="33"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d33">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.CC/2–2245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HWA1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-22T21:00:00-04:00"
                            >February 22, 1945—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>391. British Embassy has just informed us that at Yalta <persName
                        corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> made a plea for Saudi Arabia to be given an
                    opportunity to qualify for an invitation to the San Francisco Conference;<note
                        n="46" xml:id="d33fn1">See <persName corresp="#p_BCE1">Bohlen</persName>
                        Note on the meeting of the Foreign Ministers, February 11, 1945, <ref
                            target="frus1945Malta#pg_931">
                            <hi rend="italic">Conferences at Malta and Yalta</hi>, p.
                        931</ref>.</note> that <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName>
                    <pb facs="0147" n="85" xml:id="pg_85"/> was unable to agree then but promised to
                    consider the matter; that <persName corresp="#p_CK1">Clark Kerr</persName> has
                    been instructed to express the hope that Soviet Government will now agree Saudi
                    Arabia be given hint that if she does declare a state of war and adhere to
                    United Nations Declaration by March 1, she will be invited to San Francisco;
                    that Mr. <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> hopes the Department will
                    support this proposal.</p>
                <p>We feel very strongly that Saudi Arabia, because of her firm friendship and
                    valuable assistance to our cause, should be given an opportunity to qualify as a
                    United Nation by entering into a state of war with Germany or Japan or both and
                    permitted to attend San Francisco Conference. Please consult with <persName
                        corresp="#p_CK1">Clark Kerr</persName> immediately and then make known to
                        <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> the view of this
                    Government.</p>
                <p>Secretary <persName corresp="#p_SERJ1">Stettinius</persName> concurs.</p>
                <p>Because of the March 1 deadline it is important that we have a prompt reply.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
